               <head source="#WinternitzKeith1905">Śubhaoandra’s Pāṇḍavapurāṇa, A. D. 1637.</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary source="#WinternitzKeith1905">The Pāṇḍavapurāṇa, more properly entitled the Mahābhārata, of Śubhacandra, pupil of Vijayakīrti, being a Jaina version of the Mahābhārata, written in the kāvya style, mainly in ślokas, in a. d. 1552.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="sa">Sanskrit.</textLang>
                  
               </msContents>
